## Stack

- [FastAPI](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/) + [Uvicorn](https://www.uvicorn.org/)
- [SQLAlchemy](https://www.sqlalchemy.org/) + [Alembic](https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org/)
- [pydantic-settings](https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/concepts/pydantic_settings/) for configuration
- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) for dependency management
- [ruff](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/) for linting and formatting
- [pytest](https://docs.pytest.org/) for testing

## Getting started

```bash
uv sync
cp secret/.env.example secret/.env  # fill in real values
uv run alembic upgrade head
uv run python main.py
```

The API will be available at `http://localhost:8000`, docs at `http://localhost:8000/docs`.

## Development

```bash
uv run pre-commit install   # once, sets up git hooks
uv run ruff check .
uv run ruff format .
uv run pytest
```

## Project layout

```
src/
    app.py                 FastAPI app instance
    config.py               Settings (env vars, paths, environment)
    database.py             DB session management
    exceptions.py           Custom exceptions
    exception_handlers.py   FastAPI exception handler registration
    logging_config.py       Logging setup
    load_data/               Data import / seeding logic
    models/                  SQLAlchemy models
    repositories/            DB interaction logic
    routes/                  API route definitions (orchestration)
    schemas/                 Pydantic schemas
    services/                Pure business logic
alembic/                    DB migrations
secret/                     .env files (never commit .env)
tests/
    unit/                    Unit tests (services, pure logic)
    integration/             Integration tests (DB, API)
```

## Releases

This project uses [release-please](https://github.com/googleapis/release-please) for versioning
and changelog generation, driven by [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/).
Every push to `main` is linted and tested; a merged release-please PR builds and pushes a
Docker image to `ghcr.io`.

